Please note, if you fail to reschedule your test within the required time period you will lose your test fee.
I understand that if I cancel my test within 5 business days of my test date, I will lose my test fee. Yes - I agree
IMPORTANT - MUST READ Should you wish to cancel your Driver Theory Test booking, you must do so no later than 5 business days (to include 3 complete business days) prior to your test date.
Please note, if you fail to reschedule your test within the required time period you will lose your test fee.
I understand that if I cancel my test within 5 business days of my test date, I will lose my test fee. Yes - I agree

IMPORTANT - MUST READ You have chosen to book your test in one of the test centres currently running the SAFE2 pilot programme in association with the RSA and the Department of Social Protection (Dublin Central and Wicklow).
By continuing with you your booking you are agreeing to participate in the programme.
The SAFE2 pilot programme applies to Category BW candidates only (Car, Tractor and Work Vehicles).
Please note; Category BW candidates who wish to schedule a theory test after October 12th in Dublin Central or Wicklow, please click here.
To apply for a Motorcycle (Category AM), Truck (Category C) or Bus (Category D) Theory Test, please click here to proceed.

Alternatively, if you have already completed the SAFE2 Registration process, or if you would like to complete the Driver Theory Test without participating in the pilot programme, please click here to proceed.

Mura dtugaim na nithe sin liom, tuigim nach mbeidh cead agam an tástáil a dhéanamh agus go gcaillfidh mé mo tháille thástála.

IMPORTANT - MUST READ Before proceeding with your booking, please ensure that you agree to the following statements:

Please Note; only drivers who have passed a Full Category C (Truck) Theory Test or full Category D (Bus) Theory Test on or after September 30th, 2014, are eligible to sit a Bus or Truck Module Theory Test.
Bus Module Test: You have chosen to schedule the Bus Module Theory Test.
PLEASE NOTE: You are only eligible to sit this exam if you have completed and passed the Full Truck Theory Test on or after September 30th, 2014.
If you have completed and passed the Full Truck Theory Test before this date, you need to cancel this exam and schedule the Full Bus Theory Test.
You need to do this 5 business days before your scheduled date otherwise you will forfeit your fee.
ID CARD: From June 16th 2017, any person sitting a Driver Theory Test will be required to present a Public Services Card (PSC) at the Test Centre as proof of ID.
I understand that if I do not bring my PSC I will not be allowed to test and will lose my test fee.
To book, reschedule or cancel your Bus Module Test please call our Candidate Services Team on 1890 606 106 (Lo-call rate) Monday to Friday from 8AM to 6PM.

TÁBHACHTACH – LE LÉAMH Sula leanfaidh tú ar aghaidh le háirithint a dhéanamh, cinntigh le do thoil go n-aontaíonn tú leis na ráitis seo a leanas: ní bheidh ach tiománaithe a fuair pas i lánTástáil Teoirice Chatagóir C (Trucail) nó i lánTástáil Teoirice Chatagóir D (Bus) amhail 30 Meán Fómhair 2014 nó níos déanaí incháilithe do Thástáil Teoirice Modúil Bhus nó Trucaile a dhéanamh.
Tástáil Modúil Bus:Tá sé roghnaithe agat an Tástáil Teoirice Modúil Bus a sceidealú.
TABHAIR DO D'AIRE LE DO THOIL: Níl tú incháilithe don tástáil sin a dhéanamh ach amháin sa chás gur chuir tú an lánTástáil
Teoirice Tiomána Trucail i gcrích agus go bhfuair tú pas inti amhail 30 Meán Fómhair 2014 nó níos déanaí.

Sa chás gur chuir tú an lánTástáil Teoirice Tiomána Trucail i gcrích agus go bhfuair tú pas inti roimh an dáta sin, beidh ort an tástáil sin a chur ar ceal agus an lánTástáil Teoirice Tiomána Bus a sceidealú ina hionad.
Beidh ort é sin a dhéanamh 5 lá oibre ar a laghad roimh an dáta sceidealaithe nó caillfidh tú do tháille.
Chun do Thástáil Teoirice Tiomána a sceidealú nó a chur ar ceal, Téigh i dteagmháil lenár bhFoireann Seirbhísí d'Iarrthóirí, (a bhíonn ar fáil ó 8am go 6pm)
Luan go hAoine (seachas laethanta saoire poiblí) ar 1890 606 106 (ráta Íosghlao)
